div.l:
For us it is right to celebrate the earth-shaking son of Cronus,
                       returning a good deed to our beneficent neighbor, the lord of horse-racing
                       and chariots;

These men truly are spoken of as honored in Thebes from the beginning;
                       they have good relations with the neighboring towns, and are bereft of loud
                       arrogance. And as for the memorials that fly through all the world,
